article.headline: Davidson 65, Princeton 50
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. (AP) -- Ian Johnson led three players in double-digit scoring with 15 points as Davidson knocked off Princeton 65-50 on Sunday. Boris Meno came off the bench to score 13 points and grab five rebounds while Jason Morton had 12 points and five rebounds for the Wildcats (13-7, Southern Conference). Kenny Grant posted 10 assists. Kyle Koncz led two players in double-figure scoring with 12 points while Scott Greenman added 11 for the struggling Tigers (3-12, Ivy League). The Wildcats led 37-29 at the half and converted 11 Princeton turnovers into 14 points. Davidson made 13-of-16 from the line (81.3 percent).
